Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing a suitable system for flying robots using inertial and monocular vision measurements. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper deals with monocular vision systems and odometry/tracking. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper may involve some machine learning techniques for fusing the inertial and monocular data. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possibility as the paper deals with designing a system for flying robots and estimating metric distances. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention any AI techniques, but it may involve some AI-based approaches for fusing the data.
